## Local flora as a "pharmacy"

* Plants are attacked by the same broad classes of parasites and pathogens as animals.
* Plants are attacked by insect and vertebrate herbivores -- <span style="color: red;">organisms with nervous systems</span>.
* Plants have evolved $10^5 - 10^6$ unique chemical structures, with about 5,000-15,000 per species, most of which play a role in plant defense or pollinator signaling [@medema2021].
* Many plant defensive chemicals are <span style="color: red;">neurotoxins</span>.

## Neanderthal medication? [@weyrich2017]

There are reports of self-medication in 71 species from 7 mammalian orders, with the most reports in Primates (46 species), Carnivores (10 species), and Rodents (5 species) [@neco2019n].

